The paper discusses the synthesis of lenses, which are a type of program used for bidirectional transformations of data. This topic falls under the area of programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG), as the paper uses techniques from type-directed program synthesis and information theory to guide the search process. The paper also discusses the implementation of the synthesis procedure in the Boomerang language, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the implementation on benchmark examples, which could fall under databases (cs.DB) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
